25|$|In {{the early}} 1980s, the EEOC and some federal courts began holding that sexual <b>harassment</b> <b>is</b> also {{prohibited}} under the Act. In 1986, the Supreme Court held in Meritor Savings Bank v. Vinson, , that sexual <b>harassment</b> <b>is</b> sex discrimination and is prohibited by Title VII. Same-sex sexual harassment {{has also been}} held in a unanimous decision written by Justice Scalia to be prohibited by Title VII (Oncale v. Sundowner Offshore Services, Inc., , 118 S.Ct. 998).|$|E
