25|$|One of the {{difficulties}} in understanding sexual <b>harassment,</b> <b>is</b> that it involves a range of behaviors. In most cases (although not in all cases) {{it is difficult for}} the victim to describe what they experienced. This can be related to difficulty classifying the situation or could be related to stress and humiliation experienced by the recipient. Moreover, behavior and motives vary between individual cases.|$|E
